This layer adds some recipes to boot2qt used for the swupdate talk at qtdevcon 2022. It was tested with:
MACHINE=verdin-imx8mp

Dependencies
============

  URI: https://code.qt.io/cgit/yocto/meta-boot2qt.git/
  branch: 6.3

Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the meta-embear layer to your build
 II. Building the embear-boot2qt image
III. Building the embear-boot2qt SDK


I. Adding the meta-embear layer to your build
=================================================

Run 'bitbake-layers add-layer meta-embear'

II. Building the embear-boot2qt image
========

Run 'bitbake embear-boot2qt-image'

III. Building the embear-boot2qt image
========

Run 'bitbake embear-boot2qt-image -c populate_sdk'
